message.content: Rewriting the fraction $\frac{x}{y}$ with "quantity-per-unit" language, we have $x$ is $0.9$ of $y$. Since $x$ is closer to $1$ than $0$, it follows that $x>y/2$. If this is the case, $x+y>1.5y$, which implies $399>1.5y$, so $y<266$. This leaves us with three possible integral values for $y$: $y=1,2,...,265$. Testing the vast majority of the values for $y$, one should find $y=234$ as a solution, whereby $x=210$. This gives $y-x=234-210=\boxed{24}$.
